                <head>294. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On January 5, 1959, Secretary of the Treasury <persName>Anderson</persName> led a
                    U.S. Delegation to Ottawa for the fourth meeting of the Joint U.S.-Canadian
                    Committee on Trade and Economic Affairs. During the 2-day meeting,
                        <persName>Anderson</persName>, Under Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName>, Assistant Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName>, and other U.S. officials discussed
                    with Canadian Minister of Finance <persName>Donald Fleming</persName>, and the
                    Ministers of External Affairs, Trade and Commerce, Justice, and Agriculture the
                    following topics:</p>
                <p>January 5: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>The economic outlook for North America</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>The world economy</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>January 6: <list>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Measures affecting trade between the two countries</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Agricultural surpluses and disposal policies</item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>U.S. foreign assets control procedures</item>
                        <label>6.</label>
                        <item>Effects on Canadian companies of U.S. anti-trust actions</item>
                        <label>7.</label>
                        <item>A joint communiqué</item>
                        <label>8.</label>
                        <item>The International Development Association</item>
                        <label>9.</label>
                        <item>Other business</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>A 28-page summary record of the meetings, prepared by the U.S. Delegation, is in
                    Department of State, Conference Files: Lot 64 D 560, CF 1191. A set of
                    background papers and documentation on the preparations for the meeting is <hi
                        rend="italic">ibid</hi>., CF 1186–1190. The U.S. paper on the scope and
                    objectives of the meeting is printed as <ref target="#d295">Document 295</ref>.
                    For text of the joint communiqué issued on January 6, see <hi rend="italic"
                        >American Foreign Policy: Current Documents, 1959</hi>, pages 493–496.</p>
            </div>
